Zoom simulation examples.

These are simulations with high resolution particles isolated to a single
region of the box and low resolution background particles (PartType2)
elsewhere. These examples should be run including the --zoom runtime option.

These examples are not CI-only assets. They are intended to remain useful as
general zoom-region examples for local testing, debugging, and documentation,
with CI simply reusing them as lightweight runtime checks.

Current examples:

- UniformDMGravity:
  Uniform high-resolution dark matter in a central zoom region, with
  lower-resolution uniform dark matter in the background. Uniform here means 
  uniform at the top level cell level, i.e. the particles are placed with 64 
  particles randomly distributed in each background and zoom top-level cell.

- UniformDMGravityWithHoles:
  As above, but with carved holes near the outskirts of the high-resolution
  region to exercise empty zoom-cell edge cases.
